  "description": "Along with Greek, Latin, and Mathematics, Astronomy counts as one of the oldest continuously taught subjects in the Brown curriculum. It is the study of the properties of stars, galaxies, and the Universe, combining elements from Physics and Planetary Geology. Students complete introductory coursework in classical mechanics, relativity, and astrophysics, along with mathematics and electromagnetism, then go on to study stellar and extragalactic astrophysics and cosmology. Facilities available to concentrators include the historic Ladd Observatory.",
